  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD-based prediction of wear-driven fluid film pressure distribution in a total knee replacement tibial tray under physiological gait loading. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case contact stress and fluid film conditions for a Class II orthopedic implant at Model Risk Level 3. Full 13-factor assessment: all factors addressed with rigor appropriate to MRL 3; 9 factors fully assessed, 4 factors scoped-out with documented rationale. Complete profile with inline sensitivity analysis, applicability constraint, and operating envelope.",
