        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "NCV: method of manufactured solutions convergence order within 10% of theoretical",
        "description": "Spatial convergence order demonstrated via method of manufactured solutions (MMS) must be within 10% of the theoretical second-order accuracy for the pressure-velocity coupling scheme. Iterative convergence residuals must fall below 1×10⁻⁶ for all transported quantities."
      },
      "rationale": "MMS study on a 2-D Couette geometry with non-Newtonian viscosity confirmed observed spatial order of 1.92 (theoretical 2.0; 4% deviation). Iterative residuals reached 8×10⁻⁷ for all equations within 800 iterations across the full operating envelope. Required and achieved levels both at 2."
