        "description": "Richardson extrapolation-based Grid Convergence Index (GCI) must be less than 2% for the peak fluid film pressure quantity of interest, computed on a minimum three-mesh refinement sequence with refinement ratio r ≥ 1.3. The fine-grid solution must be used for all subsequent analyses."
      },
      "rationale": "Three-mesh study (coarse 1.2M, medium 3.1M, fine 7.8M hexahedral elements; r = 1.37) yielded GCI_fine = 1.4% for peak fluid film pressure and GCI_fine = 1.7% for contact area centroid location. Both within the 2% criterion. Fine mesh selected for production runs. Required and achieved levels both at 3."
    },
