        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions: experimental boundary conditions match simulation inputs within ±5%",
        "description": "Measured experimental boundary conditions (axial load, cadence, fluid temperature, insert geometry) must match the corresponding simulation inputs within ±5% for all validation experiments. Deviations exceeding this threshold must be explicitly propagated as input uncertainty."
      },
      "rationale": "Pin-on-disc and pressure-film experiments were conducted at 37 °C ± 0.5 °C, cadence 80 steps/min ± 2 steps/min, and axial load 2.5× BW ± 3%. All deviations within the ±5% criterion. Geometry was digitised from the same implant components used in simulation using structured-light scanning (±0.05 mm). Required and achieved levels both at 2."
