        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison: NWF prediction within 15% of experimental mean with overlapping 95% CI",
        "description": "The predicted normalized wear factor (NWF) must lie within 15% of the experimental mean NWF from pin-on-disc coupon testing, and the 95% confidence intervals of simulation and experiment must overlap. Systematic bias must be less than 8% across the full operating envelope matrix."
      },
      "rationale": "Across 15 validation cases spanning the operating envelope, mean predicted NWF deviated from experimental mean by 6.3% (max 13.8%), well within the 15% criterion. Confidence intervals overlapped in all 15 cases. Systematic bias was 4.1%. Achieved level 3 is consistent with quantitative agreement metrics and uncertainty overlap. Required and achieved levels both at 3."
