        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance: peak fluid film pressure and NWF directly linked to clinical wear endpoint",
        "description": "The quantities of interest (peak fluid film pressure, contact area, NWF) must be demonstrably linked to the clinical endpoint (in vivo polyethylene wear rate) through a documented mechanistic rationale or published literature correlation. At least one peer-reviewed publication must support the QoI-to-clinical-endpoint mapping."
      },
      "rationale": "Peak fluid film pressure and NWF are mechanistically linked to UHMWPE wear via Archard's law and elasto-hydrodynamic lubrication theory. The mapping is supported by three peer-reviewed publications (Fregly et al. 2012, Zhao et al. 2018, Liu et al. 2021) and corroborated by ISO 14243-1 test methodology. Achieved level 3 reflects documented literature support exceeding the minimum requirement."
    },
    {
