        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Use error: independent peer review of simulation setup and results interpretation",
        "description": "An independent reviewer (not involved in model development) must review the simulation setup files, boundary condition assignments, and results interpretation prior to acceptance. Review findings must be documented and resolved. Simulation setup must be reproducible from archived input files."
      },
      "rationale": "An independent CFD engineer (not part of the development team) reviewed all boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and post-processing scripts. Three minor discrepancies were identified and corrected (two boundary condition labels, one unit conversion). Final simulation setup was archived in the institutional repository and successfully reproduced by a third party. Required and achieved levels both at 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-ortho-cf-10-model-form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty for the elasto-hydrodynamic lubrication equations is scoped out at MRL 3 for this COU because the governing equations (Reynolds equation with Hertzian contact) are well-established in the peer-reviewed literature for UHMWPE-on-metal contacts and have been independently validated by multiple groups. A dedicated model form assessment is deferred to the MRL 4 pathway for Class III device applications. This scoping decision is documented in the project risk register (ref: ORTHO-RISK-2024-017)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-ortho-cf-11-model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-11-modelinputs",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs: all material properties and boundary conditions traceable to measured data with documented uncertainty",
        "description": "All model inputs (synovial fluid viscosity, UHMWPE elastic modulus, tibial tray geometry, gait loading profiles) must be traceable to primary measurement data with documented measurement uncertainty. Uncertainty must be propagated through the model using Monte Carlo or equivalent method (minimum 500 samples)."
      },
      "rationale": "Synovial fluid viscosity characterised by rotational rheometry (n=12 donors, 37 °C; CV 8.3%). UHMWPE elastic modulus from nanoindentation (n=30; CV 4.1%). Tibial tray geometry from structured-light scanning (±0.05 mm). Gait loading from ISO 14243-1 standard profiles with ±3% load uncertainty. Monte Carlo propagation (1000 samples) performed; peak pressure 95% CI ±9.2%. All inputs archived with provenance metadata. Required and achieved levels both at 3."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-ortho-cf-12-test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Test sample characterisation beyond geometry and bulk material properties is scoped out for this COU because the validation strategy relies on standardised ISO 14243-compliant UHMWPE coupons with certified material certificates. Detailed microstructural characterisation (crystallinity, oxidation index) is outside the scope of the wear-prediction COU and is addressed in the separate material qualification assessment (ref: ORTHO-MAT-QA-2024-003)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-ortho-cf-13-equiv-input",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the validation experiment and the COU is partially addressed through the test conditions factor (CF-04) and model inputs factor (CF-11). A separate equivalency assessment is scoped out at MRL 3 because the validation experiments were conducted on the same implant geometry and within the same operating envelope as the COU. Full equivalency mapping is deferred to the MRL 4 pathway. This decision is documented in the project V&V plan (ref: ORTHO-VVP-2024-002, Section 4.3)."
    }
